This API allows users to:

Send a question to the AI agent.

The agent processes the question using Gemini.

The response is returned through a FastAPI endpoint.

Example flow:

User → FastAPI endpoint → Agent → Gemini Model → Response → User

Technologies Used

Python

FastAPI

OpenAI Agents SDK

Gemini API

Async Programming

dotenv

Logging

Concepts of OpenAI Agents SDK I Used
1. AsyncOpenAI Client

First, I created an OpenAI-compatible client to communicate with the Gemini API.

client = AsyncOpenAI(
    api_key=gemini_api_key,
    base_url="https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/"
)
Why I used this

The AsyncOpenAI client allows the OpenAI Agents SDK to communicate with APIs that follow the OpenAI API format.

In this case, I connected it to Google Gemini instead of OpenAI.

2. OpenAIChatCompletionsModel

Then I configured the model.

model = OpenAIChatCompletionsModel(
    model="gemini-flash-lite-latest",
    openai_client=client
)
Why I used this

This class allows the Agents SDK to interact with chat completion models.

It defines:

which model to use

which client will call the model

3. Agent

Next, I created an Agent.

agent = Agent(
    name="Assistant",
    instructions="You are a helpful assistant.",
    model=model
)
Why I used this

An Agent represents the AI system that receives instructions and generates responses.

It contains:

agent name

instructions (system prompt)

model configuration

This allows us to create reusable AI agents.

4. RunConfig

I created a RunConfig to control how the agent runs.

config = RunConfig(
    model=model,
    model_provider=client,
    tracing_disabled=True
)
Why I used this

RunConfig allows us to configure:

which model is used

the provider client

tracing or logging behavior

5. Runner

The Runner is responsible for executing the agent.

result = await Runner.run(
    agent,
    query.question,
    run_config=config
)
Why I used this

The Runner:

sends input to the agent

handles model execution

manages the full agent workflow

returns the final response

FastAPI Integration

I used FastAPI to expose the agent as an API.

Home Endpoint
GET /

Returns:

Gemini Agent API Running Successfully

This confirms that the API server is working.

Ask Agent Endpoint
POST /ask

Request Body:

{
  "question": "What is artificial intelligence?"
}

The request is sent to the agent, and the model generates a response.

Response Example:

{
  "response": "Artificial intelligence is the simulation of human intelligence in machines..."
}
Environment Variables

I used dotenv to securely load the Gemini API key.

load_dotenv()
gemini_api_key = os.getenv("GEMINI_API_KEY")

This prevents exposing API keys in the source code.

Logging

I implemented logging to track application behavior.

logging.basicConfig(
    level=logging.INFO,
    format="%(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s"
)

Logging helps monitor:

API requests

errors

agent responses

Async Programming

This project uses async functions to handle API requests efficiently.

Example:

async def ask_agent(query: Query):

and

await Runner.run(...)

Async programming improves performance and scalability when dealing with multiple requests.

Project Workflow

The workflow of this project is:

User sends a request to /ask

FastAPI receives the request

Runner executes the agent

Agent sends request to Gemini model

Model generates a response

Response is returned to the user

What I Learned From This Project

While building this project, I learned:

How the OpenAI Agents SDK works

How to create and configure AI Agents

How to connect Gemini using OpenAI-compatible APIs

How to use Runner to execute agents

How to configure execution using RunConfig

How to build an AI API with FastAPI

How to handle async model execution

How to manage environment variables securely

How to implement logging for backend applications

